            h1.ui.header.large#learn-title
                .content
                    i.book.icon
                    | Red Flag 6: Demand for Secrecy 
            .ui.centered.stackable.grid
                .eight.wide.column
                    p If the caller <strong> persistently requests and implies that you should keep the accident a secret </strong> from other family members, friends, and anyone involved in this case, such as bank representative. It is a Big Red Flag. They often use the following excuses:
                    
                    .ui.bulleted.list
                        .item <strong> Excuse 1: </strong> It is too “embarrassing” to let their parents know, and they “don't want to worry anyone.” However, they promise to let their parents know after things get resolved.
                    
                    .callout
                        .dark-blue-square
                            img(src=user.avatarImg, alt='avatar picture')
                        .light-blue-content
                            h3.call-header Important
                            p This tactic is used to convince you that you're the only person they trust. They want you to believe that you're their favorite and most trustworthy family member, aiming to prevent you from reaching out to others to confirm the scammer's true identity.

                .eight.wide.column
                    h3 Audio Example
                    p Grandparent: Yes, yes, I'll do it right away. Just hold on. Everything will be okay, sweetheart. Should I tell your parents?
                    p Scammer: No, no, please don't tell them yet, Grandpa. They'll only worry, and I don't want them to stress out more than they already are. Let's keep this between us for now, okay?
                    p Grandparent: Okay, I understand, dear. I won't say anything. Just focus on getting better.
